1
00:00:31,537 --> 00:00:35,953
BEYOND THE BAR

2
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:40,123
This is where I keep all my treasures.

3
00:00:41,166 --> 00:00:44,211
-I wish I could live here for a day.
-This is amazing.

4
00:00:44,294 --> 00:00:45,879
Wait, hold on.

5
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:49,675
Isn't this Seo Won-mi's Meet the Body?

6
00:00:49,758 --> 00:00:51,468
As expected, you know your stuff.

7
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:58,058
But what about these covered up pieces?

8
00:00:59,518 --> 00:01:02,521
I'm extra careful when it comes
to preserving my most cherished pieces.

9
00:01:03,564 --> 00:01:04,731
Careful…

10
00:01:04,815 --> 00:01:08,443
Have you heard
of the up-and-coming breakout artist

11
00:01:08,527 --> 00:01:09,903
named Ryu Gwan‑mo?

12
00:01:09,987 --> 00:01:12,155
I know him. I saw him on the news.

13
00:01:12,239 --> 00:01:13,740
He's really famous.

14
00:01:13,824 --> 00:01:15,951
He graduated from
a prestigious art school in the US

15
00:01:16,034 --> 00:01:17,536
and even exhibited at the Marte Museum.

16
00:01:17,619 --> 00:01:21,081
The Marte Museum is a fixture in Chelsea.

17
00:01:21,164 --> 00:01:23,417
They only invite
really famous artists to exhibit there.

18
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:26,295
It took a lot of effort
to acquire one of his pieces.

19
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:28,338
For how much?

20
00:01:29,965 --> 00:01:31,300
For 300 million won?

21
00:01:31,383 --> 00:01:32,509
-Three hundred?
-Unreal.

22
00:01:32,593 --> 00:01:35,178
What does a 300-million-won painting
even look like?

23
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:36,972
Now, it's time

24
00:01:37,055 --> 00:01:41,018
to reveal Ryu Gwan‑mo's Fiesta.

25
00:01:50,902 --> 00:01:52,571
You're kidding, right?

26
00:01:53,196 --> 00:01:55,073
-What do you mean?
-How much was that?

27
00:01:55,907 --> 00:01:57,034
Three hundred million?

28
00:01:58,660 --> 00:02:00,037
Have you lost your mind?

29
00:02:00,704 --> 00:02:02,164
What's wrong with you?

30
00:02:02,247 --> 00:02:03,206
Listen,

31
00:02:03,707 --> 00:02:05,292
I have that painting at home.

32
00:02:06,543 --> 00:02:09,046
-What?
-I also have the same one at home.

33
00:02:11,465 --> 00:02:13,967
Ye-jin, you really need
to stop lying like that.

34
00:02:14,051 --> 00:02:14,926
I'm lying?

35
00:02:23,477 --> 00:02:25,270
-Hey, Mom.
-Hey, Ye-jin.

36
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:27,648
-Are you home?
-Yes.

37
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:30,567
Can you show us the painting
in the master bedroom?

38
00:02:30,651 --> 00:02:32,402
Sure. Hold on.

39
00:02:42,287 --> 00:02:44,122
Thanks, Mom. Bye.

40
00:02:45,791 --> 00:02:48,126
I wonder who's actually lying here.

41
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,212
You paid 300 million won for that?

42
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:52,255
That's hilarious.

43
00:02:52,798 --> 00:02:54,841
I got that painting a while ago
from a flea market

44
00:02:54,925 --> 00:02:56,051
for 100,000 won.

45
00:03:00,347 --> 00:03:01,515
What? 100,000 won?

46
00:03:02,683 --> 00:03:03,558
You got a knockoff.

47
00:03:04,768 --> 00:03:06,061
A copy of this work.

48
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:07,979
That makes more sense.

49
00:03:08,063 --> 00:03:11,608
I guess someone was selling
replicas of Fiesta at the flea market.

50
00:03:11,692 --> 00:03:14,194
Isn't this the date
when the painting was finished?

51
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:18,240
September 2024. That's six months ago.

52
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:19,991
So?

53
00:03:20,075 --> 00:03:22,119
I bought that painting a year ago.

54
00:03:24,454 --> 00:03:25,455
What?

55
00:03:26,206 --> 00:03:30,502
Yours is the knockoff.

56
00:03:30,585 --> 00:03:33,922
Seo-yeong, you haven't changed one bit.

57
00:03:34,005 --> 00:03:37,634
Do you remember when I called out
your knockoff shoes in middle school?

58
00:03:37,718 --> 00:03:39,469
You insisted they were real,

59
00:03:40,095 --> 00:03:43,348
but when we asked the store,
they confirmed the shoes were fake.

60
00:03:43,432 --> 00:03:44,766
That was so funny.

61
00:03:46,727 --> 00:03:48,979
You still haven't fixed that bad habit?

62
00:03:49,062 --> 00:03:51,606
I mean, I heard you made a bit of money

63
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:54,568
from reselling clothes
with swapped out labels,

64
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:56,361
so I assumed you stopped all that.

65
00:03:57,487 --> 00:03:58,530
But I guess

66
00:03:59,364 --> 00:04:01,283
leopards can't change their spots.

67
00:04:02,451 --> 00:04:04,494
Swapped out… labels?

68
00:04:05,912 --> 00:04:07,122
Watch it.

69
00:04:07,205 --> 00:04:10,000
Don't run your mouth
when you don't know anything.

70
00:04:10,083 --> 00:04:13,003
And what will you do
if it turns out yours is the knockoff?

71
00:04:13,628 --> 00:04:16,381
That is highly unlikely,
but on the off chance it is,

72
00:04:18,341 --> 00:04:19,509
I will tattoo

73
00:04:20,218 --> 00:04:22,387
"I am a knockoff" on the back of my neck.

74
00:04:24,055 --> 00:04:26,975
But if yours is the knockoff,
you'll get a tattoo that says

75
00:04:27,893 --> 00:04:29,603
"Knockoff addict."

76
00:04:31,855 --> 00:04:33,273
-What?
-What's wrong?

77
00:04:34,065 --> 00:04:34,941
Scared?

78
00:04:36,401 --> 00:04:37,486
No.

79
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:39,488
Not one bit.

80
00:04:40,322 --> 00:04:42,199
All right. You're on.

81
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:44,701
Did you hear that?

82
00:04:44,785 --> 00:04:45,952
-Yeah.
-Yes.

83
00:04:55,837 --> 00:05:00,759
SALIERI'S MONOLOGUE

84
00:05:04,346 --> 00:05:05,347
I'm pregnant.

85
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:07,849
I'm six months along.

86
00:05:12,979 --> 00:05:14,231
Sorry if I startled you.

87
00:05:15,607 --> 00:05:16,900
The timing was never right.

88
00:05:18,443 --> 00:05:19,611
How…

89
00:05:22,364 --> 00:05:23,240
How could you?

90
00:05:23,323 --> 00:05:25,909
How could I have a baby
with Won-jun when I told you

91
00:05:26,868 --> 00:05:28,537
I didn't want one with you?

92
00:05:30,622 --> 00:05:31,915
I had a change of heart.

93
00:05:33,333 --> 00:05:36,419
How can you just say something like that…

94
00:05:38,171 --> 00:05:39,047
so easily?

95
00:05:39,130 --> 00:05:41,007
Because it's the truth.

96
00:05:41,091 --> 00:05:43,051
Once I got to my late thirties,

97
00:05:44,511 --> 00:05:47,806
my view on having children changed.

98
00:05:48,515 --> 00:05:51,434
Don't make this about you.
This has nothing to do with you.

99
00:05:51,518 --> 00:05:52,811
Nothing to do with me?

100
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:55,021
In my twenties and early thirties,

101
00:05:55,772 --> 00:05:57,482
I just wanted to focus on myself.

102
00:06:01,403 --> 00:06:04,322
I think you could've been
a good father too.

103
00:06:05,907 --> 00:06:09,202
If you had stayed by my side,

104
00:06:10,161 --> 00:06:11,830
this could've been your baby.

105
00:06:19,713 --> 00:06:21,673
I still feel sorry about that.

106
00:06:23,884 --> 00:06:25,093
I decided on my own

107
00:06:26,303 --> 00:06:28,388
to take away your chance to be a father.

108
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:31,600
Oh, and your cologne.

109
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:34,102
I guess the baby doesn't like it.

110
00:06:35,562 --> 00:06:37,230
My morning sickness has been bad.

111
00:06:37,772 --> 00:06:40,066
I made you six months' worth
and sent it all at once.

112
00:06:41,109 --> 00:06:43,194
I'll make you more after I have the baby.

113
00:06:59,419 --> 00:07:01,755
So, to summarize,

114
00:07:01,838 --> 00:07:04,591
Ms. Lee Seo-yeong purchased
your piece Fiesta

115
00:07:04,674 --> 00:07:06,927
for 300 million won,

116
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:09,554
but Ms. Hwang Ye-jin
claims she purchased the same piece

117
00:07:09,638 --> 00:07:13,016
for 100,000 won
before Fiesta was completed.

118
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:16,645
So now, Ms. Lee Seo-yeong has filed

119
00:07:16,728 --> 00:07:19,606
a lawsuit against you
for fraud and copyright infringement,

120
00:07:19,689 --> 00:07:21,733
but she has agreed to drop all the suits

121
00:07:21,816 --> 00:07:25,320
if the court rules that the piece
she bought is the original

122
00:07:25,403 --> 00:07:27,989
and Ms. Hwang Ye-jin's piece
is a counterfeit.

123
00:07:28,073 --> 00:07:29,616
Yes. Never in my life have I…

124
00:07:31,368 --> 00:07:33,119
experienced…

125
00:07:34,955 --> 00:07:36,665
an insult like this.

126
00:07:38,583 --> 00:07:39,960
As if copying it wasn't enough,

127
00:07:40,043 --> 00:07:43,296
how could they sell it at a flea market
and not even at a gallery?

128
00:07:43,380 --> 00:07:46,299
And for a measly 100,000 won, no less.

129
00:07:46,383 --> 00:07:50,762
And that thieving brat

130
00:07:50,845 --> 00:07:52,931
who has humiliated me like this…

131
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:55,642
I will bury them.

132
00:07:56,977 --> 00:08:01,189
Please pursue every action
available under the law.

133
00:08:01,856 --> 00:08:03,191
Yes, sir.

134
00:08:04,693 --> 00:08:05,986
Oh God.

135
00:08:13,201 --> 00:08:16,162
I think this is the main building.

136
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:18,206
It's not the annex?

137
00:08:18,289 --> 00:08:21,126
It's just been constant indigestion.
I feel a bit nauseous.

138
00:08:21,209 --> 00:08:23,878
You should get that checked out.
Death spares no one.

139
00:08:23,962 --> 00:08:25,005
Oh, please.

140
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:27,799
-We need to go to the annex.
-Yes.

141
00:08:27,882 --> 00:08:29,801
-I just need digestive medicine.
-Hold on.

142
00:08:30,635 --> 00:08:31,511
Excuse me.

143
00:08:32,053 --> 00:08:34,639
This is the annex building.

144
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:36,016
Where are you going?

145
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:39,853
Administration.

146
00:08:41,896 --> 00:08:45,066
Just take a left at this corner
and you'll find it.

147
00:08:45,859 --> 00:08:48,903
-She knows sign language.
-You're pretty good at it.

148
00:08:48,987 --> 00:08:50,321
Thank you.

149
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:57,871
When did you learn sign language?

150
00:08:57,954 --> 00:08:59,122
Do you go to church?

151
00:08:59,748 --> 00:09:00,623
What?

152
00:09:00,707 --> 00:09:03,126
A lot of people learn
sign language at church.

153
00:09:04,169 --> 00:09:05,086
No, I don't.

154
00:09:06,129 --> 00:09:07,839
It's a bit of a long story.

155
00:09:07,922 --> 00:09:10,050
What do you mean? Where did you learn it?

156
00:09:14,012 --> 00:09:15,138
Jeez, you scared me.

157
00:09:16,973 --> 00:09:17,891
What?

158
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:22,353
INTRO TO KOREAN SIGN LANGUAGE

159
00:09:23,563 --> 00:09:27,942
So, you want me to read this book
and teach you sign language?

160
00:09:28,026 --> 00:09:29,986
-Yes.
-Why would I do that?

161
00:09:30,070 --> 00:09:33,073
I can't read because of my dyslexia.

162
00:09:33,156 --> 00:09:34,616
-So?
-That's why

163
00:09:34,699 --> 00:09:37,786
I'm asking you to read it
and then teach me.

164
00:09:39,454 --> 00:09:40,371
I'm a senior.

165
00:09:40,455 --> 00:09:41,539
I am too.

166
00:09:41,623 --> 00:09:42,874
For the third time.

167
00:09:42,957 --> 00:09:45,043
I mean, why are you suddenly trying…

168
00:09:46,211 --> 00:09:47,212
to learn sign language?

169
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:49,214
She wants to meet her twin sister.

170
00:09:49,297 --> 00:09:51,174
She wants to be able to talk with her.

171
00:09:51,257 --> 00:09:53,927
I've always wanted to see her again.

172
00:09:54,803 --> 00:09:56,429
I feel like when I do,

173
00:09:57,806 --> 00:09:59,474
this spell will be broken.

174
00:10:01,726 --> 00:10:02,602
My dyslexia, I mean.

175
00:10:15,907 --> 00:10:19,452
Hyo-ju, it's really nice to see you.
We finally get to meet. I missed you.

176
00:10:22,372 --> 00:10:24,833
Do you remember me?

177
00:10:30,922 --> 00:10:32,590
Are you sure that was right?

178
00:10:33,383 --> 00:10:35,718
Yeah, of course.

179
00:10:35,802 --> 00:10:37,762
It doesn't seem like she understands.

180
00:10:38,847 --> 00:10:40,890
Maybe you learned English sign language

181
00:10:41,724 --> 00:10:43,226
and not Korean Sign Language.

182
00:10:45,895 --> 00:10:46,771
You can just talk.

183
00:10:47,480 --> 00:10:49,732
I can read lips too.

184
00:10:56,239 --> 00:10:58,366
Oh, is that what happened?

185
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:00,869
Yeah, that's when I learned

186
00:11:01,536 --> 00:11:04,747
that not all deaf people
rely exclusively on sign language.

187
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:08,585
Hyo-min's sister knew
both sign language and lipreading.

188
00:11:08,668 --> 00:11:10,044
What is lipreading?

189
00:11:10,670 --> 00:11:14,340
It's watching someone's mouth movements
to understand what they're saying.

190
00:11:16,718 --> 00:11:19,179
I see. Lipreading…

191
00:11:24,726 --> 00:11:27,979
PLAINTIFF'S CLAIM SUMMARY

192
00:11:33,318 --> 00:11:34,652
MY SISTER
PHOTO SENT

193
00:11:43,286 --> 00:11:44,829
COMPLAINT
PLAINTIFF: RYU GWAN-MO

194
00:11:44,913 --> 00:11:46,122
DEFENDANT: MOON JEONG-HYE

195
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:52,921
Hyo-ju, what is this?

196
00:11:56,341 --> 00:12:00,053
A friend of mine received this complaint,
and it seemed serious.

197
00:12:00,553 --> 00:12:02,388
I was wondering
if my talented lawyer sister

198
00:12:02,472 --> 00:12:04,098
could take a look at it for her.

199
00:12:05,308 --> 00:12:07,101
Okay.

200
00:12:07,185 --> 00:12:08,937
I'll text you after I take a look.

201
00:12:12,732 --> 00:12:14,150
CLAIM FOR DAMAGES

202
00:12:14,234 --> 00:12:15,109
PLAINTIFF: RYU GWAN-MO

203
00:12:18,154 --> 00:12:21,866
COUNSEL FOR PLAINTIFF: LEE & SEO
HAN SEONG-CHAN, MIN SO-RA

204
00:12:28,498 --> 00:12:32,252
The plaintiff is Ryu Gwan-mo.
Isn't he a famous artist?

205
00:12:32,335 --> 00:12:34,796
And the firm representing him
is Lee & Seo.

206
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:36,339
It does look serious.

207
00:12:36,422 --> 00:12:40,009
She probably got it a while ago.
Why wait so long to bring it up?

208
00:12:40,093 --> 00:12:42,637
Well, she's a bit young

209
00:12:42,720 --> 00:12:45,807
and has never gotten something like this,
so she just let it sit on her desk.

210
00:12:45,890 --> 00:12:48,810
I found it today
and rushed to send it to you.

211
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:53,982
DEFENDANT: MOON JEONG-HYE
COPYRIGHT INFRINGEMENT, ETC.

212
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:59,153
SUPREME COURT E-LITIGATION
SEARCH BY CASE NUMBER

213
00:12:59,237 --> 00:13:00,947
MOON JEONG-HYE

214
00:13:02,782 --> 00:13:04,367
JUDGMENT DATE

215
00:13:07,829 --> 00:13:10,081
The judgment date is at two o'clock today.

216
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:12,667
What is that?

217
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:15,920
The complaint was served,
but she failed to respond within 30 days

218
00:13:16,004 --> 00:13:19,215
or appear in court,
so the judgment date was set.

219
00:13:19,299 --> 00:13:20,675
And that's today.

220
00:13:22,051 --> 00:13:24,012
So? Is that bad?

221
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:28,224
At this rate,
the plaintiff will win by default.

222
00:13:28,308 --> 00:13:31,769
Then, the defendant,
your friend Jeong-hye,

223
00:13:31,853 --> 00:13:34,772
will only be able to contest the decision
with an appeal.

224
00:13:35,398 --> 00:13:38,693
I don't fully understand,
but I'm guessing it doesn't look good?

225
00:13:38,776 --> 00:13:41,029
Yes, she needs to go to court immediately

226
00:13:41,112 --> 00:13:43,614
and submit a request to cancel
the default judgment hearing.

227
00:13:46,075 --> 00:13:47,785
Can you do that for her?

228
00:13:48,411 --> 00:13:50,955
Of course. For your friend, I can.

229
00:13:52,081 --> 00:13:53,916
Thanks, Hyo-min.

230
00:13:59,172 --> 00:14:00,965
COURT

231
00:14:01,049 --> 00:14:03,217
Submission of the Power of Attorney form
was confirmed.

232
00:14:03,301 --> 00:14:05,762
Let's cancel the judgment hearing for now.

233
00:14:06,429 --> 00:14:08,348
Thank you, Your Honor.

234
00:14:08,431 --> 00:14:10,767
However, since there is
an ongoing criminal case

235
00:14:10,850 --> 00:14:13,936
related to the dispute involving
the plaintiff, Mr. Ryu Gwan-mo,

236
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:16,564
I can't give you that much time.

237
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:18,358
I see.

238
00:14:19,442 --> 00:14:22,904
Submit your answer within a week
and adhere to the deadline.

239
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:24,113
Did you say one week?

240
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:28,493
Yes, Your Honor.

241
00:14:29,452 --> 00:14:30,578
Understood.

242
00:14:40,713 --> 00:14:41,589
Come in.

243
00:14:45,093 --> 00:14:46,844
-Mr. Lee.
-What's up?

244
00:14:54,811 --> 00:14:55,895
What's that?

245
00:14:55,978 --> 00:14:58,314
COMPLAINT
COPYRIGHT INFRINGEMENT, ETC.

246
00:14:58,940 --> 00:14:59,941
Ms. Kang.

247
00:15:01,025 --> 00:15:03,820
You should've consulted a senior attorney
before taking on a new case.

248
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:06,447
It was very urgent,
and she's my sister's friend--

249
00:15:06,531 --> 00:15:09,283
Did you forget already?
About the mess I had to clean up

250
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:11,828
after you ran off to investigate
the city gas case.

251
00:15:11,911 --> 00:15:14,080
But everything worked out in the end…

252
00:15:15,498 --> 00:15:16,916
I'm sorry, sir.

253
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,336
And the retainer fee?

254
00:15:20,420 --> 00:15:22,130
I was hoping we could do it pro bono?

255
00:15:22,213 --> 00:15:23,381
PRO BONO: FREE LEGAL SERVICE

256
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:25,341
That requires special authorization.

257
00:15:25,967 --> 00:15:27,343
You're driving me nuts.

258
00:15:27,844 --> 00:15:29,846
For the sake of argument,
let's say we get approval.

259
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:31,556
You only have a week to prepare.

