in your previous works.

558
00:31:19,961 --> 00:31:23,215
Can you tell us what led you
to experiment with this new approach?

559
00:31:23,965 --> 00:31:27,594
When I was at SAIC…
You know what that is, right?

560
00:31:27,677 --> 00:31:30,138
SAIC.
School of the Art Institute of Chicago.

561
00:31:33,225 --> 00:31:34,684
You must know…

562
00:31:35,602 --> 00:31:38,647
It is a world-renowned art school

563
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:40,941
that has produced
waves of artistic geniuses…

564
00:31:41,817 --> 00:31:44,820
A specialty school.
Isn't that common knowledge?

565
00:31:46,488 --> 00:31:48,281
Perhaps not,
if you're unfamiliar with art.

566
00:31:48,365 --> 00:31:51,535
That must be why
you represent someone like that.

567
00:31:52,536 --> 00:31:56,373
Cut him off. Don't just let him babble on.

568
00:31:56,456 --> 00:31:59,626
The witness should limit
his answers to counsel's questions.

569
00:32:00,335 --> 00:32:01,503
Let me ask again.

570
00:32:02,045 --> 00:32:05,215
Can you tell us what led you
to experiment with this new approach?

571
00:32:05,882 --> 00:32:07,509
An artist's personal experiences

572
00:32:08,552 --> 00:32:13,473
and emotional shifts
have a profound impact

573
00:32:14,141 --> 00:32:16,852
on their work.

574
00:32:17,394 --> 00:32:19,646
A short while before I produced Fiesta,

575
00:32:20,355 --> 00:32:22,983
