576
00:32:23,900 --> 00:32:26,445
When I held my child

577
00:32:26,528 --> 00:32:29,573
in my arms for the very first time,

578
00:32:29,656 --> 00:32:32,617
I felt happiness, joy,

579
00:32:33,118 --> 00:32:36,455
and new emotions about humankind.

580
00:32:36,538 --> 00:32:38,498
All of that had
a profound effect on my work.

581
00:32:38,582 --> 00:32:40,542
In my previous work,
the beauty of empty space

582
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:44,004
and the harmony of black
and white were pronounced.

583
00:32:44,087 --> 00:32:45,297
With my piece, Fiesta…

584
00:32:46,506 --> 00:32:50,510
With "my piece," Fiesta,
I utilized a drip technique

585
00:32:50,594 --> 00:32:53,597
and a unique matière technique
I personally developed

586
00:32:54,222 --> 00:32:56,433
to produce a work

587
00:32:56,516 --> 00:32:59,644
with playful allure, rooted in vivid hues.

588
00:32:59,728 --> 00:33:01,354
La fiesta.

589
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:06,568
It means "party" in Spanish.

590
00:33:11,239 --> 00:33:13,283
That's what it is. A party.

591
00:33:14,951 --> 00:33:16,203
The birth of a baby.

592
00:33:18,955 --> 00:33:21,666
Can you explain the drip
and matière techniques?

593
00:33:22,918 --> 00:33:24,085
The drip technique

594
00:33:25,045 --> 00:33:28,465
involves pouring paint
directly onto the canvas.

595
00:33:28,548 --> 00:33:32,385
The matière technique
is quite a unique method that is used

596
00:33:32,469 --> 00:33:34,221
to create visual texture.

597
00:33:34,304 --> 00:33:36,515
-I see--
-In my piece, Fiesta,

598
00:33:37,015 --> 00:33:40,101
I made subtle adjustments to both
the water ratio and paint amount

599
00:33:40,185 --> 00:33:45,023
to ensure perfectly predictable,
precise dripping that became the base

600
00:33:45,106 --> 00:33:46,399
for a striking visual effect--

601
00:33:46,483 --> 00:33:47,817
Yes, thank you.

602
00:33:48,985 --> 00:33:50,320
That's how I made it.

603
00:33:51,947 --> 00:33:53,031
Yes.

604
00:33:55,075 --> 00:33:58,370
It's clear Ryu Gwan-mo is
the originator of this new technique.

605
00:34:05,794 --> 00:34:07,963
As an artist, the work you produced…

606
00:34:10,131 --> 00:34:11,091
I mean, come on.

607
00:34:11,591 --> 00:34:15,262
They'll call just about anyone
an artist these days.

608
00:34:15,345 --> 00:34:17,055
Please calm down, sir.

609
00:34:17,556 --> 00:34:18,431
My goodness.

610
00:34:19,140 --> 00:34:21,643
As an artist, all the art you produced--

611
00:34:21,726 --> 00:34:22,811
Jeez. What? "Art"?

612
00:34:22,894 --> 00:34:25,647
Plaintiff, compose yourself.

613
00:34:26,982 --> 00:34:29,401
The defense counsel may continue.

614
00:34:31,695 --> 00:34:35,824
As an artist, all the art you produced
shares a common style.

615
00:34:35,907 --> 00:34:39,035
Can you explain how you came about
adopting your techniques?

616
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:42,956
Yes, well, I…

617
00:34:43,039 --> 00:34:43,999
I…

618
00:34:51,131 --> 00:34:53,967
So…

619
00:34:57,721 --> 00:34:59,055
I just drew it.

620
00:35:01,891 --> 00:35:05,770
When you were younger, you went
to an amusement park with your dad

621
00:35:06,396 --> 00:35:07,939
-and saw a colorful parade--
-Your Honor.

622
00:35:08,023 --> 00:35:10,650
Objection. Leading the witness.

623
00:35:11,568 --> 00:35:12,527
Counsel,

624
00:35:13,486 --> 00:35:17,866
leading questions are prohibited
when examining your own witness.

