00:53:32,501 --> 00:53:35,045
when she was 12 years old.

893
00:53:36,380 --> 00:53:40,592
After he left, her mother
burned all photos of him.

894
00:53:46,306 --> 00:53:48,475
And because her mother got mad

895
00:53:48,559 --> 00:53:50,519
every time she mentioned her father,

896
00:53:50,602 --> 00:53:54,481
Jeong-hye could no longer talk about him.

897
00:53:58,277 --> 00:53:59,903
Dad left.

898
00:53:59,987 --> 00:54:02,489
He doesn't live with us anymore.

899
00:54:03,323 --> 00:54:06,618
When Jeong-hye could not talk
about how she missed her dad,

900
00:54:06,702 --> 00:54:09,747
she decided to draw him instead.

901
00:54:10,289 --> 00:54:14,460
However, she loved her mother so much

902
00:54:14,543 --> 00:54:17,171
that she decided to draw him in secret

903
00:54:17,880 --> 00:54:21,091
to avoid making her mother sad.

904
00:54:22,718 --> 00:54:26,638
This was possible for Jeong-hye, who was
an artistic genius and a tetrachromat.

905
00:54:30,017 --> 00:54:31,560
All her paintings looked like

906
00:54:31,643 --> 00:54:34,646
vibrant landscapes on the surface,

907
00:54:34,730 --> 00:54:37,983
but when lit
at a certain illuminance in the dark,

908
00:54:38,066 --> 00:54:40,986
the carefully hidden image
of her father would appear.

909
00:54:42,279 --> 00:54:44,406
With her innate gift,

910
00:54:44,490 --> 00:54:47,576
she was able to make every stroke
without ever making a mistake

911
00:54:47,659 --> 00:54:49,244
to meticulously layer

912
00:54:49,328 --> 00:54:52,748
visual textures, color intensity,
and contrast in value.

913
00:54:53,707 --> 00:54:56,752
And by using fluorescent colors,

